This paper proposes a deep learning-based denoising method for CT images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The method uses a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular deep learning technique in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The paper also analyzes the f-GAN objective, which is a type of neural network loss function commonly used in the neural network (cs.NE) community. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which may be of interest to the multimedia (cs.MM) community.
